<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" lasteditedby="Adam" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Acceleration-Nominal</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Motion Definition:<keyword translate="true">Nominal Acceleration</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para><table styleclass="MotionPupup" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">Nominal Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the acceleration as defined by the mathematical function of the Motion-Law and the Blend-Point motion-values. The </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">nominal acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is shown in the Acceleration Graph. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Machine elements will </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">always</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> experience accelerations significantly more than the </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">nominal acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. If there is a step change in acceleration, the actual acceleration can be two times, and even more, than the nominal values.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
